The Wilderness God Wars Dungeon is a multi-combat area located within a cave east of The Forgotten Cemetery in the level 28 Wilderness. It contains monsters from the main God Wars Dungeon. The cave was opened to the monsters when an underground tremor caused a deep fissure to open up, which caused the creatures to climb through the fissure and populate the cave. Like the main God Wars Dungeon, all monsters in the dungeon are aggressive to any player unless they have equipped at least one item that is devoted to their god. The entire area counts as the Wilderness. Players will be able to attack you here.

Contents

  • 2 God-related protection

  • 4 Wilderness Diary
  • 5 Changes
  • 6 Trivia

Getting there[edit | edit source]

As the dungeon is located within the Wilderness, players must go through the wilderness to get to the wilderness God Wars Dungeon. Methods of getting to the dungeon include:

  • Using the Wilderness Obelisk. The closest obelisk is the level 27 obelisk, located slightly east-southeast of the entrance. The Wilderness Obelisk system can be quickly accessed from one's player owned house (80 construction required), or by teleporting to the Corporeal Beast's cave and running southeast to the level 19 obelisk. Completion of the hard tier of the Wilderness diary allows the player to select the destination obelisk.
  • Casting the Cemetery Teleport spell on the Arceuus spellbook or the corresponding tablet to The Forgotten Cemetery and running east
  • Casting the Dareeyak Teleport spell on the Ancient spellbook or breaking a Dareeyak teleport tablet to the ruins at level 23 Wilderness. Both require completion of Desert Treasure in order to use.
  • Using a burning amulet teleport to the Bandit Camp and running west then north.
  • Using the agility shortcut from Trollheim puts you much closer than running directly from Edgeville, but requires 64 Agility.
  • Running directly to the dungeon from Edgeville.

God-related protection[edit | edit source]

Main article: God Wars Dungeon § God-related protection

The dungeon[edit | edit source]

The location of the different armies.

The dungeon has a small, empty cavern that splits apart into two different paths; one will lead to a large boulder which can be moved with 60 Strength(boostable), or pass through a jutting wall which requires 60 Agility(boostable). A small crevice is behind the obstacle, which can be used to enter the main dungeon. The Agility path drops players off near Bandos' encampment, while the Strength path drops players off near Armadyl's encampment.

This empty cavern is a single-way combat zone. The large cavern in which the followers fight in is a multi-way combat zone.

The Wilderness God Wars Dungeon works the same way as the main dungeon - players can wear the respective god equipment to make monsters aligned to their god unaggressive, along with the typical aggressive monsters that initiate combat with other monsters. However, due to the layout of the faction "camps" in the dungeon, the fighting only usually takes place in the centre and southern areas of the dungeon.

The main attraction of the dungeon is the ecumenical key, which all monsters in the dungeon can drop. Players can have up to 3, 4 or 5 of these keys in their bank, which can be increased as more Wilderness Diary tasks are completed. The keys allow players to skip the 40 killcount needed to enter the general's room in the regular God Wars Dungeon. The aviansies in this dungeon also drop noted adamantite bars.

The dungeon is also visited by players on slayer assignments, mostly for Spiritual creatures due to being far easier to access and those assigned potential monsters inside by Krystilia.

Wilderness Diary[edit | edit source]

There are 4 tasks of the Wilderness Diary to be completed in this area:

  • Enter the dungeon (medium)
  • Kill a Bloodveld (medium)
  • Kill a Spiritual warrior (hard)
  • Slay a Spiritual mage (elite)

Changes[edit | edit source]

Date Changes
10 September 2015
(update)

It is no longer possible to use the Jutting Wall entrance to the Wilderness GWD to avoid damage.

30 July 2015
(update)

The boulder at the Wilderness God Wars Dungeon entrance has changed how it treats damage that is queued on you as you pass through it.

16 October 2014
(update)

You can no longer avoid taking damage permanently using the Wilderness God Wars Dungeon obstacles.

Trivia[edit | edit source]

  • The dungeon lacks several followers compared to the main dungeon:
    • Saradomin priests do not appear in the dungeon.
    • Bandosian hobgoblins, jogres and cyclopes do not appear in the dungeon.
